Feature: Regenerative Technology Bootstrap

  As a community bootstrapping regenerative capacity
  I want to invest simultaneously in physical, knowledge, and governance infrastructure
  So that each investment makes the others more possible

  Background:
    Given the global manufacturing capacity produces $12.3T annual gross output
    And 1.2 billion workers operate across 220 EJ energy consumption
    And 90 billion tonnes of raw material extraction occurs annually
    And the current industrial capacity is locked into extractive patterns

  Scenario: Bootstrap pathway avoids Earth's suboptimal decisions
    Given fossil fuel lock-in, nuclear stagnation, and TSMC geographic concentration exist
    And pharmaceutical API dependency on China persists at scale
    And linear economy maintains only 9% plastic recycling
    When the community invests in regenerative infrastructure
    Then circular systems replace extractive patterns over time
    And bootstrap planning includes engineering and governance together

  Scenario: Industrial capacity serves as both problem and resource
    Given the manufacturing base provides regenerative build potential
    When the community needs energy, materials, and knowledge coordination
    Then circular systems are built without recreating 620 EJ/year of industrial power
    And the bootstrap sequence moves from survival through advanced industry

  Scenario: Physical, knowledge, and governance infrastructure invest together
    Given investment in physical infrastructure includes energy, water, and materials
    And investment in knowledge infrastructure includes coordination systems, governance protocols, and skill repositories
    And investment in governance infrastructure includes Ostrom-principle commons, reputation systems, and dispute resolution
    When one investment area grows
    Then it makes the other two investment areas more possible
    And no single investment area can succeed alone

  Scenario: Knowledge layer enables community-scale coordination
    Given supply chain software, GPS logistics, and marketplace platforms coordinate global manufacturing
    When the same digital infrastructure serves community-scale regenerative systems
    Then knowledge coordination operates without starting from scratch
    And the community configures existing infrastructure for regenerative purposes

  Scenario: Suboptimal decisions had technical and governance roots
    Given thorium LFTR was abandoned for weapons-program reasons
    And pharmaceutical API concentration was driven by IP maximalism
    When the community makes technical decisions
    Then governance implications are evaluated alongside engineering choices
    And the same failure modes are prevented in the bootstrap sequence

  Scenario: Bootstrap success requires three simultaneous investments
    Given investment in physical infrastructure alone
    And investment in knowledge infrastructure alone
    And investment in governance infrastructure alone
    When any single investment operates without the others
    Then the system collapses
    And all three must grow together to reach advanced industry phase
